# Wanderlust Trips - Travel Website

A simple, responsive travel website demo showcasing popular destinations, tour packages, and booking information.

## Features

- **Header Navigation** - Easy-to-use navigation menu with links to all sections
- **Hero Section** - Eye-catching banner with call-to-action
- **Destinations** - Grid display of 4 popular travel destinations (Maldives, Paris, Bali, New York)
- **Tour Packages** - Sample tour packages with pricing and duration
- **How It Works** - 3-step booking process explanation
- **Testimonials** - Customer reviews and ratings
- **Blog Section** - Travel tips and guides
- **Newsletter** - Email subscription form
- **Contact Form** - Demo contact form for inquiries
- **Footer** - Links and social media placeholders

## File Structure
```text
/ (project root)
├─ index.html                 # Main HTML page (ties together layout, sections, and components)
├─ README.md                  # Project documentation (this file)
├─ css/
│  └─ styles.css              # Core stylesheet (the provided CSS)
├─ js/
│  └─ main.js                 # Optional scripts: nav toggle, form handlers, small interactions
├─ assets/
│  ├─ images/                 # Hero, destinations, testimonials, blog thumbnails
│  └─ icons/                  # SVGs or icon sprites
├─ data/
│  └─ destinations.json       # Sample data for destinations / packages (optional)
├─ dist/ or build/            # Production-ready build output (if using a bundler)
├─ .gitignore                 # Files/folders to ignore in git
└─ package.json               # Dev scripts and dependencies (optional)
```